      • percentage_Conversion_Into_Hex_Should_Be_Correct

        @ParameterizedTest
@ValueSource(ints={0,1,2,50,73,99,100})
public void percentage_Conversion_Into_Hex_Should_Be_Correct​(java.lang.Integer percent)
        Convert incoming percentage value 0 - 100% to an integer in base sixteen 00 - FF (0 - 255). Where 100% = 255 and 1% = 2.55 (Rounding.HALF_UP) accordingly but as two hex digits (e.g. 00, 03, 7F, FF)

      • pointTextColors_Without_setTextOpacity_Should_Starts_With_Max_Opacity_Value_FF

        @ParameterizedTest
@ValueSource(strings={"#000088","#ff0000","#ffffff","#374b5c"})
public void pointTextColors_Without_setTextOpacity_Should_Starts_With_Max_Opacity_Value_FF​(java.lang.String hexColor)
        Color and opacity (alpha) values are expressed in hexadecimal notation. The range of values for any one color is 0 to 255 (00 to ff). For alpha, 00 is fully transparent and ff is fully opaque. The order of expression is aabbggrr, where aa=alpha (00 to ff); bb=blue (00 to ff); gg=green (00 to ff); rr=red (00 to ff). For example, if you want to apply a blue color with 50 percent opacity to an overlay, you would specify the following: <color>7fff0000</color>, where alpha=0x7f, blue=0xff, green=0x00, and red=0x00.

      • pointTextColors_With_setTextOpacity_Should_Starts_With_Opacity_Value_But_Not_Default_FF

        @ParameterizedTest
@ValueSource(strings={"#000088","#ff0000","#ffffff","#374b5c"})
public void pointTextColors_With_setTextOpacity_Should_Starts_With_Opacity_Value_But_Not_Default_FF​(java.lang.String hexColor)
        Color and opacity (alpha) values are expressed in hexadecimal notation. The range of values for any one color is 0 to 255 (00 to ff). For alpha, 00 is fully transparent and ff is fully opaque. The order of expression is aabbggrr, where aa=alpha (00 to ff); bb=blue (00 to ff); gg=green (00 to ff); rr=red (00 to ff). For example, if you want to apply a blue color with 50 percent opacity to an overlay, you would specify the following: <color>7fff0000</color>, where alpha=0x7f, blue=0xff, green=0x00, and red=0x00.
